README.md
# BEWA Conference Website Setup Guide

This guide will help you publish your BEWA Conference website using GitHub Pages.

## ðŸ“¦ Step 1: Unzip the Folder

Unzip the downloaded folder to your computer. It contains all the necessary files:

- `index.html`
- `old-school.html`
- `using-ai.html`
- `globiz-education.html`
- `style.css`
- `README.md`

## ðŸš€ Step 2: Create a GitHub Repository

1. Go to [github.com](https://github.com) and sign in  
2. Click the **+** icon in the top right and choose **New repository**  
3. Name it `bewa-conference-site`  
4. Choose **Public** and click **Create repository**

## ðŸ“¤ Step 3: Upload Your Files

1. On your new repository page, click **Add file > Upload files**  
2. Drag and drop all the files from the unzipped folder  
3. Click **Commit changes**

## ðŸŒ Step 4: Enable GitHub Pages

1. Go to **Settings** > **Pages**  
2. Under **Source**, choose `main` branch and `/root`  
3. Click **Save**

Your site will be live at:



